            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1721398663152-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1721398666446-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1721398666446-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1721398666446-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1721398666446-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1721398666446-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>a little of the<strong> pickling liquid</strong> from the onion in a separate bowl – this is your <strong>turmeric yoghurt dressing</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong>, then wash your<strong> spinach </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Drain the<strong> quick-pickled</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and discard the liquid</p><p>Add the <strong>drained lentils</strong> and <strong>spinach </strong>to the pot with the cooked rice</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1721398670510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1721398670510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1721398670510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1721398670510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1721398670510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sultanas</strong> and <strong>diced apricots</strong> to the rice with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook over a medium heat for 2-3 min or until everything is warmed through and most of the spinach has wilted</p><p>Remove the pot from the heat and add the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>with the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>quick-pickled onion</strong> – these are your<strong> mixed grains</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> curried free range chicken</strong> finely on a clean board</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1721398673905-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1721398673905-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1721398673905-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1721398673905-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1721398673905-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced curried free range chicken</strong> and <strong>roast onion wedges</strong> over the <strong>mixed grains</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>turmeric yoghurt dressing </strong>all over and garnish with the<strong> remaining quick-pickled onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
